ðŸ”€ Multiplexing
Multiple apps on one device can communicate over the same network.

TCP/UDP + Port Numbers = we know exactly where data is going.

Client: 10.0.0.1
Server: 10.0.0.2

Connections:
- TCP 3000 -> 80 (HTTP)
- UDP 7100 -> 5004 (VoIP)
- TCP 4407 -> 143 (Email)
ðŸ’¬ Notes
TCP ensures delivery, UDP doesnâ€™t care â€” speed > reliability.

Port numbers are not security â€” they're just directions.

HTTPS and SSH use TCP because accuracy is critical.

VoIP uses UDP because it's real-time â€” no time to resend!

